<div class="tip_number">TIP 198</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            Adolescents or young adults who experience headaches that get progressively more severe over a few days or longer, along with visual changes, may have a rare but treatable condition in which the pressure on the brain is increased. While not usually life threatening, it can cause serious complications such as a permanent loss of vision.
        </div>

</div>
